From the Publisher

CHECKLIST FOR USING FRONTLINE PLUS

  • Your cat is at least eight weeks old
  • Your cat weighs at least 1kg
  • Your cat shows no signs of lesions or feeling unwell. If they show any of these signs, you should not apply the product and see a veterinary surgeon

No flea product can stop fleas jumping onto your pets. It is normal to see a few fleas on your pet after treatment as new fleas continue to hatch out from infested environments. These fleas will be killed within 24 hours of jumping onto your treated pet.

HOW TO APPLY

Simply follow these easy steps:

Previous page

  1. REMOVE

    Remove 1 pipette from the pack and its blister.

  2. SNAP

    Hold the pipette upright facing away, tap the neck and snap off the tip along the scored line.

  3. APPLY

    Part your cat's fur at the base of the neck and apply directly onto the skin in 1 spot.

  4. RELAX, YOUR CAT IS NOW TREATED

    The treatment will naturally spread over the skin. Remember not to bathe your cat for 2 days after.

Next page

Directions

About this item KILLS FLEAS - Fleas jumping onto your treated dog are killed within 24 hours, preventing infestations from building up KILLS TICKS - Ticks latching onto your treated dog are killed within 48 hours, helping to reduce the risk of disease transmission TRIED AND TRUSTED - FRONTLINE's original vet-strength formula has an exemplary safety profile EASY APPLICATION - Simply empty one pipette onto your dog's skin at the back of the neck and it will quickly spread over their coat - it's as easy as that TREAT MONTHLY - It’s important to treat your pets year-round to prevent flea and tick infestations. One 3-pack provides your dog with 3 months of protection.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Ella Madoo
1.0 out of 5 stars Does not work, save yourself the trouble
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 25 November 2023
Size Name: 3 PipettesVerified Purchase
This was our first time treating our cat for fleas - we noticed she had them so went straight to find a product to do the job. We went off the recommendation of my partners family that use this product on their cat and they said it works for them.

The use of the product was easy enough, instructions are relatively clear and not too much confusion which is always nice. We treated our cat in the evening and that seemed to be it pretty simple.

I had thought that her symptoms seemed to improve, I was under the impression that we were seeing less flee dirt around so assumed it worked. I had already decided I was going to give her a bath once she was clear to do so as the product recommended you do not bath them for 2 days.

It was about a week later and I gave her a bath and once we finished and I was drying her I noticed a flea on her neck which I wasn’t sure was dead or not. I got it out and realised it was alive, and when I picked her up to dry her back legs I saw she was teeming with fleas still!

I had a look around and got the impression that I must have not applied it properly as she is a long haired cat it may have not gotten on her skin enough. So I figured I’d have to follow the instructions and wait for 3 more weeks till I could re-apply.

We went about a week and it just got ridiculous she was so uncomfortable and was constantly grooming and we were getting flea dirt and eggs all over the place so I decided to call up the vets and get her an appointment.

After speaking to the vets they informed me that this product simply does not work on modern fleas! The formulas that pet shop and retail products can use is around 30 years old now and is essentially entirely ineffective on fleas that have developed a resistance to the formula. Where once upon a time I’m sure this product was brilliant, unfortunately it no longer does the trick.

I really was not impressed when finding this out, having spent extra on the “Frontline Plus” to find out that it doesn’t even do the basic requirement is very underwhelming and frustrating. It is not fair on pet owners or pets to market this as a valid product and seemingly more high end than others available only for it to not work and cause prolonged unnecessary discomfort for the animals.

Since first using this we have also found out that my partner’s family who made the initial recommendation is now also having issues with their cat and dog regarding fleas and have also had to go to the vet for the same thing so it seems it is not a stand alone issue.

A very disappointing outcome in our experience.
